The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	 West Bengal Police rallied to beat HAL, Lucknow 2-1 in a Beighton Cup match on Thursday. Arun Kumar Trivedi put HAL ahead in the 31st minute before Jugan Minzs brace (45th and 56th minute) turned the game the policemens way. In the days other match, Bihar Warriors defeated Howrah Union. Bikram Dhan scored a second-half goal for the winners.           
	 The Cricket Association of Bengal selection committee selected Bengal under-22 medium pacer Nilkantha Das as Ashok Dindas replacement in the senior Bengal team that will take on UP in Kanpur from December 8-11.                 
	 Treta Bhattacharya beat Aandrita Deb 6-2, 6-3 to win the womens singles title at the Floodlit tennis tournament organised by Saturday Club. The mens final will feature Farid Alam and Vinod Sewa.                
